$context = Context();
$context->variables->are(t=>'Real');

$a = random(2,10);
$x = Formula("$a*t - $a*sin(t)")->reduce->TeX;
$y = Formula("$a - $a*cos(t)")->reduce->TeX;

$ans = Formula("(64*($a**2)) * pi/ 3");

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
\{ beginproblem() \}
\{ textbook_ref_exact("Rogawski ET 2e", "11.2","31") \}
Compute the surface area of the surface generated by revolving one arch of the cycloid \( c(t) = ($a t - $a \sin t, $a - $a \cos t) \) about the x-axis.
$PAR
\{ ans_rule() \}
$PAR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS($ans->cmp);

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$SOL
One arch of the cycloid is traced as \( t \) varies from \( 0 \) to \( 2 \pi \).  Since \( x(t) = $a t - $a \sin t\) and \( y(t) = $a - $a \cos t \), we have \( x'(t) = $a - $a\cos t \) and \( y'(t) = $a\sin t \).  Hence, using the identity \( 1 - \cos t = 2 \sin^2 \frac{t}{2} \), we get
\[ x'(t)^2 + y'(t)^2 = \left( $a - $a\cos t \right) ^2 + \{$a**2\}\sin^2 t = \{$a**2\}(1 - 2 \cos t + \cos^2 t + \sin^2 t) = \{2*($a**2)\} - \{2*($a**2)\} \cos t = \{4*$a*$a\} \sin^2 \frac{t}{2} \]
By the formula for the surface area we obtain:
\[ S = 2 \pi \int ^{2 \pi} _0 y(t) \sqrt{ x'(t)^2 + y'(t)^2 } \, dt = 2 \pi \int ^{2 \pi} _0 \left( $a - $a\cos t \right) \cdot \{2*$a\} \sin \frac{t}{2} \, dt \]
\[ = 2 \pi \int ^{2 \pi} _0 \{2*$a\} \sin^2 \frac{t}{2} \cdot \{2*$a\} \sin \frac{t}{2} \, dt = \{8*$a*$a\} \pi \int ^{2 \pi} _0 \sin^3 \frac{t}{2} \, dt = \{16*$a*$a\} \pi \int ^{\pi} _0 \sin^3 u \, du \]
We use a reduction formula to compute this integral, obtaining
\[ S = \{16*$a*$a\} \pi \left[ \frac{1}{3} \cos^3 u - \cos u \right] ^{\pi} _0 = \{16*$a*$a\} \pi \left[ \frac{4}{3} \right] = \frac{\{64*$a*$a\} \pi}{3} \]
END_SOLUTION

